com.satori.rtm.model

Class SubscriptionError

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.satori.rtm.model.CommonError
      • com.satori.rtm.model.SubscriptionError

  • public class SubscriptionError
extends CommonError
    Represents the body of a Protocol Data Unit (PDU) for a subscription-specific error.

    The subscription_id field specifies the subscription_id with the error and the error field specifies the unique identifier for the error.

    The error_text field contains text that describes the error. This field is variable and may change in the future, and should not be parsed. You can use this text, for example, to include in error log files.

    The following are specific SubscriptionError errors:

    • out_of_sync error as an unsolicited error

    For more information on error messages from the RTM Service, see the RTM API Reference. 

     {
    "subscription_id": string(),
    "error": string(),
    "error_text": text(),
    "missed_message_count": count()
 }
